","dates":"May 11, 1775","notes":"With Ephraim Strong, made Milford representative at May 11, 1775 meeting"},{"title":"Justice of the Peace","jurisdiction":"Milford, Connecticut","dates":"1777"}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"military_service":[{"war":"American Revolutionary War","rank":"Lt.","unit":"Connecticut Militia","notes":"Name appears on Revolutionary War Veterans plaque, Milford Cemetery. Represented Milford at CT General Assembly May 11, 1775 alongside Ephraim Strong.","war_id":"WAR004"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Lt. John Fowler","title":"Lieutenant","first_name":"John","last_name":"Fowler","married_names":[],"bio_blurb":"Milford town clerk and justice"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"politics","header":"Three generations of Fowlers held Milford's town clerk","body":"He served as town clerk of Milford — an office inherited from his father John Fowler, who had inherited it from grandfather John Fowler. Three consecutive generations of Fowlers held the office across more than a century."},{"number":2,"category":"politics","header":"Justice of the Peace and CT General Assembly","body":"On May 11, 1775 he was appointed one of two Milford representatives to the Connecticut General Assembly. In 1777 he was appointed Justice of the Peace; he died in 1781."},{"number":3,"category":"military","header":"Revolutionary War lieutenant in Milford militia","body":"He served as lieutenant in the Connecticut militia during the Revolution. His name appears on the plaque in Milford Cemetery commemorating Revolutionary War veterans of the town."}],"career":[{"role":"Town Clerk","organization":"Milford, Connecticut"},{"role":"Justice of the Peace","organization":"Milford, Connecticut","start_year":1777},{"role":"Repr